## Answer

Pi SDK provides three mechanisms for dynamic status display during tool execution. No existing example combines `tool_execution_start/end` with `setWorkingMessage`, but the API fully supports it.

### 1. `ctx.ui.setStatus(id, text)` ‚Äî Persistent Footer Status

Shows text in footer bar until cleared. Multiple extensions can coexist via unique `id`.

```typescript
ctx.ui.setStatus("orchestrator", ctx.ui.theme.fg("accent", "‚óè Reviewing..."));
ctx.ui.setStatus("orchestrator", ctx.ui.theme.fg("success", "‚úì Sent"));
ctx.ui.setStatus("orchestrator", undefined);  // Clear
```

### 2. `ctx.ui.setWorkingMessage(text?)` ‚Äî Streaming Working Row

Replaces the "Working..." text shown during LLM streaming/tool execution.

```typescript
ctx.ui.setWorkingMessage("Reviewing code...");
ctx.ui.setWorkingMessage("Sending to API...");
ctx.ui.setWorkingMessage();  // Restore default "Working..."
```

### 3. `ctx.ui.setWorkingIndicator({frames, intervalMs?})` ‚Äî Spinner Animation

Customize the animated indicator next to working message.

```typescript
ctx.ui.setWorkingIndicator({ frames: [ctx.ui.theme.fg("accent", "‚óè")] });  // Static
ctx.ui.setWorkingIndicator({ frames: [], intervalMs: 120 });  // Hidden
ctx.ui.setWorkingIndicator();  // Restore default spinner
```

### Event Hooks for Dynamic Status

```typescript
// Tool-level hooks (fire per-tool):
// tool_execution_start ‚Üí event.toolName, event.toolCallId, event.args
// tool_execution_update ‚Üí event.toolName, event.partialResult
// tool_execution_end ‚Üí event.toolName, event.result, event.isError
// tool_call ‚Üí event.toolName, event.input (can block/modify)

// Turn-level hooks:
// turn_start ‚Üí event.turnIndex, event.timestamp
// turn_end ‚Üí event.turnIndex, event.message, event.toolResults
```

### Recommended Pattern for Dynamic Orchestrator Status

```typescript
pi.on("tool_execution_start", async (event, ctx) => {
  const labels: Record<string, string> = {
    bash: "Executing...",
    read: "Reading file...",
    write: "Writing file...",
    edit: "Editing...",
    // your custom tool names
  };
  const label = labels[event.toolName] ?? `Running ${event.toolName}...`;
  ctx.ui.setWorkingMessage(label);
  ctx.ui.setStatus("orchestrator", ctx.ui.theme.fg("accent", `‚óè ${label}`));
});

pi.on("tool_execution_end", async (event, ctx) => {
  const icon = event.isError ? "‚úó" : "‚úì";
  ctx.ui.setStatus("orchestrator", ctx.ui.theme.fg(
    event.isError ? "error" : "success",
    `${icon} ${event.toolName} done`
  ));
  ctx.ui.setWorkingMessage();  // Restore default
});

pi.on("turn_start", async (event, ctx) => {
  ctx.ui.setStatus("orchestrator", ctx.ui.theme.fg("accent", "‚óè Thinking..."));
});

pi.on("turn_end", async (_event, ctx) => {
  ctx.ui.setStatus("orchestrator", ctx.ui.theme.fg("dim", "Idle"));
});
```

## Evidence

- **extensions.md lines 2155-2256**: Full `ctx.ui` API reference for `setStatus`, `setWorkingMessage`, `setWorkingVisible`, `setWorkingIndicator`, `setWidget`, `setFooter`
- **extensions.md lines 585-604**: `tool_execution_start/update/end` event signatures with `event.toolName`, `event.toolCallId`, `event.args`, `event.result`, `event.isError`
- **extensions.md lines 535-544**: `turn_start/turn_end` with `event.turnIndex`
- **extensions.md line 2329**: "Custom working-indicator frames are rendered verbatim. If you want colors, add them to the frame strings yourself."
- **status-line.ts**: Shows `setStatus` on `turn_start`/`turn_end` with themed colors
- **working-indicator.ts**: Shows `setWorkingIndicator` with custom frames, colors, intervals
- **working-message-test.ts**: Shows `setWorkingMessage` with ANSI-colored custom text
- **custom-footer.ts**: Shows `setFooter` with `footerData.getExtensionStatuses()` reading `setStatus` values

## Caveats

- No official example combines `tool_execution_start/end` with `setWorkingMessage` for per-tool dynamic status. Pattern above is extrapolated from documented API.
- In parallel tool execution mode, multiple `tool_execution_start` events fire concurrently ‚Äî last one wins for `setWorkingMessage`. Use `setStatus` with unique IDs if you need to show all concurrent tools.
- `setWorkingMessage` only visible during active streaming/turn. `setStatus` persists in footer between turns.
- `ctx.signal` available in `tool_call`/`tool_result`/`turn_end` but may be `undefined` in idle contexts.

## Findings
- summary: Found complete API for dynamic status: `setStatus` (footer), `setWorkingMessage` (working row), `setWorkingIndicator` (spinner), plus `tool_execution_start/end` and `turn_start/end` hooks to trigger updates
- key_files: [`docs/extensions.md`, `docs/tui.md`, `examples/extensions/status-line.ts`, `examples/extensions/working-indicator.ts`, `examples/extensions/working-message-test.ts`]
- issues: No pre-existing example combining tool events + working message; pattern derived from API docs
- recommendation: Implement tool_execution_start/end handlers with setWorkingMessage + setStatus for dynamic orchestrator status. Use setStatus for persistent footer state, setWorkingMessage for transient per-tool labels.

